        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 2:50PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sturgis, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Morganfield, Waverly, Breckinridge Center, Sturgis, and Uniontown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
